            <p style="font-size: 16px;">The World Business Institute (WBI) is an international organisation solely devoted for promoting, supporting and advancing high quality academic and research activities in all disciplines of Business and Social Sciences throughout the world. It conducts, promotes and supports applied research activities though international conferences, colloquium, seminars, workshops with or without collaborative partnership with internationally recognized universities and institutes. It conducts academic programs, professional development programs and skill-based training for both the academics and professional people. Though founded in 2000 as the Business and Computing Institute of Australia, it was reconstituted as WBI, which is legally constituted and registered with the Australian Securities and Investment Commission (ASIC)- an arm of Federal Government of Australia with ABN 12 149 970 169. More than two hundreds academics having at least PhD from over 50 countries are associated with the WBI as the Fellows and they are engaged as reviewers of the conference papers, sit on the international and Scientific Committees of our conferences and Panel of Best Paper Award. In addition, they conduct seminars and workshops for academics and doctoral students. A number of academic institutions such as American University in the Emirates, UAE, National Chung Chang University, Taiwan, East Asia Institute of Management, Singapore, Shanghai University of Economics and Finance, China and University of Wollongong University-Dubai, UAE have been associated with the WBI as co-organiser of international conferences.</p>
